# List Column Header Resize (Mandatory — Do Not Regress)

**Status:** Verified working on Windows (2026-07-15, v0.8.138–0.8.141). **Code reference:** git tag **`v0.8.141`** (`ListColumnHeaderWidget`, `BlockListWidget::wireListColumnHeader`, `FeatureListPanel::wireListColumnHeader`).

Full handover: [AGENTS.md](../../AGENTS.md) — **§8.11 List column header resize**.

## Purpose

Feature list and workflow block list share **`ListColumnHeaderWidget`** above the table — **not** stock `QHeaderView` drag resize. Divider hit-test, paint guides, and drag apply live in list-specific `wireListColumnHeader` + layout structs.

## Required architecture

| Layer | Responsibility |
| ----- | -------------- |
| `ListColumnHeaderWidget` | Paint labels + `|` divider guides; ±`kDividerHalfWidthPx` hit-test; `SplitH` / `SizeVer` cursors; `WA_Hover` + `enterEvent`/`leaveEvent` |
| `BlockListWidget` / `FeatureListPanel` | `wireListColumnHeader`: providers for edges, divider Xs, handle id, `applyDrag`; persist layout in `QSettings` |
| Divider geometry | **From live table** `columnViewportPosition` + `columnWidth` (workflow) or layout math synced to list (feature) — **never** layout-only math that drifts from painted columns |
| Pairwise resize | Drag moves **left+right neighbor** widths together (`applyPairwiseColumnResize` / feature-list switch); snapshot layout on `dividerDragStarted` |
| Workflow **요약** | `summaryWidth` stored explicitly; `reconcileSummarySlack()` fills viewport slack on resize only — **매칭** fixed width pinned right |
| Stock header | Workflow: `horizontalHeader()->hide()` + height 0 — custom header owns resize |

## Workflow block list — every divider boundary

Include **`summaryDividerX`** at **동작|요약** (left edge of summary column). `blockListDividerHandleAt` / `blockListDividerXs` must list **all** column left edges including summary, duration, …, match, and ROI when visible.

## Workflow panel vertical split

- Block list vs **블록 추가**: `UiResizeHandle::DampedSplitter` (`kSplitterDragPixelsPerStep` = 8).
- **Never** `WorkflowEditorPanel::setEnabled(false)` when no feature — disables splitter; disable edit buttons via `setEditingEnabled` + `m_feature` guard only.

## Anti-patterns (known failures — do not reintroduce)

| Do not | Why |
| ------ | --- |
| Replace with `QHeaderView::Interactive` / `Stretch` / `StretchLastSection` alone | Broken resize, inverted drag, dead handles (v0.8.119–0.8.131) |
| Divider positions from layout struct without `columnViewportPosition` | Cursor/hit-test drift from visible columns (v0.8.135) |
| Omit **동작|요약** divider | That boundary not resizable (v0.8.137) |
| `setEnabled(false)` on whole workflow panel when `!m_feature` | Vertical split not draggable (v0.8.141) |
| Custom `BlockListColumnHeader` / viewport eventFilter one-offs | Superseded by shared `ListColumnHeaderWidget` |

## Before closing header/resize UI tasks

Manually verify on Windows:

1. Workflow header: `↔` on every `|` divider including **동작|요약**; drag resizes correct neighbor pair; **요약** absorbs slack; **매칭** stays right.
2. Feature header: all four dividers (**사용|▶|기능|방식|키**) + bottom row-height edge.
3. Dark theme: `|` guides visible.
4. No feature selected: workflow vertical splitter still drags.

